## Comment Style

### Ruby Comments

```ruby
# Good: Explain WHY, not WHAT
# Using find_by instead of find to avoid raising exception
# when article doesn't exist, allowing graceful error handling
@article = Article.find_by(id: params[:id])

# Good: Document complex business logic
# Calculate tiered discount based on user membership:
# - Gold: 20% base + 5% loyalty
# - Silver: 15% base + 2% loyalty
# - Bronze: 10% flat
def calculate_discount(user)
  base_discount = tier_discount(user.tier)
  loyalty_bonus = user.gold? ? 0.05 : (user.silver? ? 0.02 : 0)
  base_discount + loyalty_bonus
end

# Bad: State the obvious
# Get the article
@article = Article.find(params[:id])

# Bad: Commented-out code (delete instead)
# def old_method
#   # old implementation
# end
```

### JavaScript Comments

```javascript
// Good: Explain non-obvious decisions
// Debounce search to avoid excessive API calls
// Wait 300ms after user stops typing
this.searchTimeout = setTimeout(() => {
  this.performSearch()
}, 300)

// Good: JSDoc for functions
/**
 * Calculates total price including tax
 * @param {Array} items - Array of item objects
 * @param {number} taxRate - Tax rate as decimal (e.g., 0.08 for 8%)
 * @returns {number} Total price with tax
 */
function calculateTotal(items, taxRate) {
  const subtotal = items.reduce((sum, item) => sum + item.price, 0)
  return subtotal * (1 + taxRate)
}
```

### ERB Comments

```erb
<%# Good: Explain view logic %>
<%# Show edit button only to article author %>
<% if @article.user == Current.user %>
  <%= link_to "Edit", edit_article_path(@article) %>
<% end %>

<%# Bad: State the obvious %>
<%# Render the article title %>
<h1><%= @article.title %></h1>
```

